  "body": "\n### Description\nThe executors we are using for building besu will be end-of-life on Dec 31, 2021:\n\nhttps://discuss.circleci.com/t/legacy-convenience-image-deprecation/41034\n\n~~It seems the latest java convenience image is based on Java-14, so we will need to ensure we are still targeting/building compatible images.  At this time we are still targeting the Java 11 LTS release for the default besu JVM~~\n\n#### Update:\nLet's decouple this update from JVM upgrades and just upgrade the container images we use for circle-ci in `besu` and `besu-native`.\nThe latest cimg for openjdk-11 is `docker pull cimg/openjdk:11.0.12`. \n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n~~* Update to the latest convenience images (cimg/openjdk:14.0)~~\n* Ensure builds are compatible with java 11 LTS \n* besu and besu-native circle-ci pipelines should use the SAME cimg to ensure libc compatibility\n\n",
